
Action: file_editor create /app/memory/PRD.md --file-text "# TalentRank AI — PRD

## Original problem statement
TalentRank AI — Explainable Candidate Intelligence & Ranking Platform. A recruiter tool that
lets users define a job, add or upload candidate resumes, and get an AI-generated ranking
with an explainable breakdown across skills, experience, education, and culture fit.

## User personas
- Recruiter / hiring manager evaluating a pipeline of candidates for one job.
- Founder / hiring lead needing a fast, defensible shortlist for a role.

## Architecture
- FastAPI backend (`/app/backend/server.py`) — MongoDB via Motor.
- Frontend: React + Tailwind + shadcn (Swiss High-Contrast design).
- LLM: Claude Sonnet 4.5 via `emergentintegrations` (Emergent Universal LLM key).
- PDF parsing: `pypdf`.

## Data model
- `jobs`: id, title, company, description, required_skills[], seniority, created_at
- `candidates`: id, job_id, name, email, headline, years_experience, education,
  skills[], resume_text, scores{overall, skills, experience, education, culture_fit},
  strengths[], gaps[], explanation, ranked, created_at

## API surface (all under `/api`)
- GET `/` — health
- GET `/stats` — pipeline stats + top 3 candidates
- POST `/jobs`, GET `/jobs`, GET `/jobs/{id}`, DELETE `/jobs/{id}`
- GET `/jobs/{id}/candidates`
- POST `/jobs/{id}/candidates` — manual add
- POST `/jobs/{id}/candidates/upload` — PDF/TXT resume upload
- DELETE `/candidates/{id}`
- POST `/jobs/{id}/rank` — batch rank all candidates with Claude Sonnet 4.5
- POST `/candidates/{id}/rerank` — re-score one
- GET `/jobs/{id}/export.csv` — download shortlist CSV

## Frontend routes
- `/` Dashboard (hero + stats + top candidates + recent jobs)
- `/jobs` Jobs list
- `/jobs/new` Job creation form
- `/jobs/:id` Job detail with leaderboard, upload/manual entry, run-ranking, export
- `/jobs/:id/compare` Side-by-side candidate comparison

## Implemented (2026-07-02) — MVP v1.0
- Full CRUD for jobs + candidates
- Resume PDF/TXT upload with basic heuristic parsing (name, email, years)
- AI ranking with explainable score breakdown, strengths, gaps
- Side-by-side comparison view
- CSV shortlist export
- Dense Swiss-style dashboard (Cabinet Grotesk / IBM Plex Sans + Mono)

## Known limits
- Emergent LLM key balance was exhausted at build time; ranking API returns \"failed\"
  until user tops up (Profile → Universal Key → Add Balance).

## Backlog (P1 / P2)
- Bulk upload with drag-and-drop zone
- Recharts radar chart for candidate comparison
- Job templates library
- Auth (JWT or Emergent Google) + multi-user tenancy
- Interview question generator from job + candidate context (per-candidate)
- Streaming ranking output over SSE for live UX
- LinkedIn / ATS integrations
